## 7. Runtime-Specific Notes

### Claude Code
- Permissions live in `.claude/settings.local.json`. Edit there, not
  here. Add to the `allow` list as friction surfaces.
- Custom skills under `.claude/skills/`. The plugin marketplace
  handles installed plugins separately.

### Codex CLI
- Skills under `.agent/skills/`. Plugin manifests use `${PLUGIN_ROOT}`
  (with `${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}` as legacy alias).

### Other runtimes (Gemini, Aider, Cursor, Windsurf)
- They each read their own file (`GEMINI.md`, `AGENT.md`,
  `.cursorrules`, `.windsurfrules`). All resolve to **this** doc via
  symlink or one-line pointer. Edit `AGENTS.md` and every runtime sees
  the change.

---

## 8. Cross-Agent Pointer Pattern

`CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `AGENT.md` (if present in repo root) are
either:

- **Symlinks** with the relative target `AGENTS.md` (same directory),
  or
- **One-line pointer files** containing the literal text `AGENTS.md`
  followed by a newline.

Both forms are valid. Agents reading their own runtime file should
resolve the pointer and load `AGENTS.md`. **Never duplicate content
across the alias files** — that is the failure mode this pattern
exists to prevent.

---

## 9. Doc Update Routing

| Change | Update |
|---|---|
| Product / scope shift | `project_requirements.md` |
| Architecture decision | `decisions.md` (append) |
| Session handoff | `handoff/current_handoff.md` (replace) |
| Task completion | `coordination/work_queue.md` (one line; detail in commit) |
| Plan delta | `plans.md` (mark landed; demote to done) |
| User-facing setup | `README.md` |

Update docs **in the same commit** as the change. A change without a
doc update rots within two sessions.

